<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
4.6.5.3. 
<taxonomicName LSID="http://zoobank.org/23A45B39-5FD0-497A-9E41-6686002FC264" authority="Djernæs &amp; Murienne, 2022" authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" status="trib. nov." tribe="Rothisilphini">Rothisilphini</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="209">trib. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="type-genus">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Type-genus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Rothisilpha" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rothisilpha" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Rothisilpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Grandcolas, 1997.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
12S: occurrence of an ATTAATT motive immediately prior to the position of primer SR-N-14594 (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2583.1995.tb00028.x" author="Kambhampati, S" journalOrPublisher="Insect molecular biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="233 - 236" refId="B36" refString="Kambhampati, S, Smith, PT, 1995. PCR primers for the amplification of four insect mitochondrial gene fragments. Insect molecular biology 4 (4): 233 - 236, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2583.1995.tb00028.x" title="PCR primers for the amplification of four insect mitochondrial gene fragments." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2583.1995.tb00028.x" volume="4" year="1995">Kambhampati and Smith 1995</bibRefCitation>
), a primer often used as the reverse 12S primer in molecular studies of cockroaches. COI barcode fragment: position 578 is a C and position 580 is a T or C.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
In all our analyses we found a strongly supported clade (pp = 100, bs 90-100) consisting of a number of genera endemic to New Caledonia: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Rothisilpha" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rothisilpha" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Rothisilpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Punctulonicus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Punctulonicus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Punctulonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Pellucidionicus" lsidName="Pellucidionicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Pellucidionicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Pallidionicus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pallidionicus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Pallidionicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Angustonicus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Angustonicus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Angustonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; all described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grandcolas, P" editor="Najt, J" journalOrPublisher="Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="91 - 124" refId="B25" refString="Grandcolas, P, 1997. Systematique phylogenetique de la sous-famille des Tryonicinae (Dictyoptera, Blattaria, Blattidae). In: Najt, J, Matile, L, Eds., Zoologia Neocaledonica, vol. 4. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris 171: 91 - 124" title="Systematique phylogenetique de la sous-famille des Tryonicinae (Dictyoptera, Blattaria, Blattidae)." volume="171" volumeTitle="Zoologia Neocaledonica, vol. 4." year="1997">Grandcolas (1997)</bibRefCitation>
. This is consistent with the results of 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" author="Legendre, F" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Experimental Zoology Part B: Molecular and Developmental Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" refId="B43" refString="Legendre, F, Nel, A, Svenson, GJ, Robillard, T, Pellens, R, Grandcolas, P, 2015. Phylogeny of Dictyoptera: dating the origin of cockroaches, praying mantises and termites with molecular data and controlled fossil evidence. Plos one 10(7): e0130127, 27 pp. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" title="Phylogeny of Dictyoptera: dating the origin of cockroaches, praying mantises and termites with molecular data and controlled fossil evidence. Plos one 10 (7): e 0130127, 27 pp." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" year="2015">Legendre et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" author="Evangelista, D" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="112 - 122" refId="B18" refString="Evangelista, D, Thouze, F, Kohli, MK, Lopez, P, Legendre, F, 2018. Topological support and data quality can only be assessed through multiple tests in reviewing Blattodea phylogeny. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 128: 112 - 122, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" title="Topological support and data quality can only be assessed through multiple tests in reviewing Blattodea phylogeny." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" volume="128" year="2018">Evangelista et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Punctulonicus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Punctulonicus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Punctulonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Pellucidionicus" lsidName="Pellucidionicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Pellucidionicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not included in these studies. Previously described species included in these New Caledonian genera were formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Princis, K" editor="Beier, M" journalOrPublisher="W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="402 - 614" refId="B67" refString="Princis, K, 1966. Blattariae: Subordo Blattoidea. Fam.: Blattidae, Nocticolidae. In: Beier, M, Ed., Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 8. W. Junk, 's-Gravenhage: 402 - 614" title="Blattariae: Subordo Blattoidea. Fam.: Blattidae, Nocticolidae." volumeTitle="Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 8." year="1966">Princis 1966</bibRefCitation>
, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1874" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Isoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Melanozosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Grandcolas, P" editor="Najt, J" journalOrPublisher="Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="91 - 124" refId="B25" refString="Grandcolas, P, 1997. Systematique phylogenetique de la sous-famille des Tryonicinae (Dictyoptera, Blattaria, Blattidae). In: Najt, J, Matile, L, Eds., Zoologia Neocaledonica, vol. 4. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris 171: 91 - 124" title="Systematique phylogenetique de la sous-famille des Tryonicinae (Dictyoptera, Blattaria, Blattidae)." volume="171" volumeTitle="Zoologia Neocaledonica, vol. 4." year="1997">Grandcolas (1997)</bibRefCitation>
placed the New Caledonian genera in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McKittrick &amp; Mackerras" authorityYear="1965" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tryonicinae">Tryonicinae</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Grandcolas, P" editor="Najt, J" journalOrPublisher="Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="91 - 124" refId="B25" refString="Grandcolas, P, 1997. Systematique phylogenetique de la sous-famille des Tryonicinae (Dictyoptera, Blattaria, Blattidae). In: Najt, J, Matile, L, Eds., Zoologia Neocaledonica, vol. 4. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris 171: 91 - 124" title="Systematique phylogenetique de la sous-famille des Tryonicinae (Dictyoptera, Blattaria, Blattidae)." volume="171" volumeTitle="Zoologia Neocaledonica, vol. 4." year="1997">Grandcolas (1997)</bibRefCitation>
together with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Methana" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Methana" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Methana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tepper" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Drymaplaneta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Drymaplaneta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Drymaplaneta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shelford" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Scabina" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scabina" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Scabina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tepper" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Temnelytra" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnelytra" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Temnelytra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see section 4.6.5.2.), 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Lauraesilpha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lauraesilpha" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Lauraesilpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Tryonicus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tryonicus" order="Isoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Tryonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see section 4.4.). 
<bibRefCitation author="Beccaloni, GW" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Systematics" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" publicationUrl="http://Cockroach.SpeciesFile.org" refId="B4" refString="Beccaloni, GW, 2014. Cockroach Species File Online., http://Cockroach.SpeciesFile.org [ [accessed November 2020] ]" title="Cockroach Species File Online" url="http://Cockroach.SpeciesFile.org" year="2014">Beccaloni (2014)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Djernæs">Djernaes</normalizedToken>
(2018) returned the New Caledonian genera to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
based on suggestions by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ode.2008.10.005" author="Murienne, J" journalOrPublisher="Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="44 - 51" refId="B59" refString="Murienne, J, 2009. Molecular data confirm family status for the Tryonicus - Lauraesilpha group (Insecta: Blattodea: Tryonicidae). Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution 9 (1): 44 - 51, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ode.2008.10.005" title="Molecular data confirm family status for the Tryonicus - Lauraesilpha group (Insecta: Blattodea: Tryonicidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ode.2008.10.005" volume="9" year="2009">Murienne (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and Legendre et 
<normalizedToken originalValue="al’s">al's</normalizedToken>
. (2015) results.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
Our results as well as those of 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" author="Legendre, F" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Experimental Zoology Part B: Molecular and Developmental Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" refId="B43" refString="Legendre, F, Nel, A, Svenson, GJ, Robillard, T, Pellens, R, Grandcolas, P, 2015. Phylogeny of Dictyoptera: dating the origin of cockroaches, praying mantises and termites with molecular data and controlled fossil evidence. Plos one 10(7): e0130127, 27 pp. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" title="Phylogeny of Dictyoptera: dating the origin of cockroaches, praying mantises and termites with molecular data and controlled fossil evidence. Plos one 10 (7): e 0130127, 27 pp." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" year="2015">Legendre et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" author="Evangelista, D" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="112 - 122" refId="B18" refString="Evangelista, D, Thouze, F, Kohli, MK, Lopez, P, Legendre, F, 2018. Topological support and data quality can only be assessed through multiple tests in reviewing Blattodea phylogeny. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 128: 112 - 122, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" title="Topological support and data quality can only be assessed through multiple tests in reviewing Blattodea phylogeny." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" volume="128" year="2018">Evangelista et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
support placing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Rothisilpha" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rothisilpha" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Rothisilpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Punctulonicus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Punctulonicus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Punctulonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Pellucidionicus" lsidName="Pellucidionicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Pellucidionicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Pallidionicus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pallidionicus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Pallidionicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandcolas" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Tryonicidae" genus="Angustonicus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Angustonicus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Angustonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a monophyletic group within 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
. Our analyses placed this group as sister to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Polyzosteriini">Polyzosteriini</taxonomicName>
consistent with 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" author="Evangelista, D" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="112 - 122" refId="B18" refString="Evangelista, D, Thouze, F, Kohli, MK, Lopez, P, Legendre, F, 2018. Topological support and data quality can only be assessed through multiple tests in reviewing Blattodea phylogeny. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 128: 112 - 122, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" title="Topological support and data quality can only be assessed through multiple tests in reviewing Blattodea phylogeny." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.05.007" volume="128" year="2018">Evangelista et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, while 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" author="Legendre, F" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Experimental Zoology Part B: Molecular and Developmental Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" refId="B43" refString="Legendre, F, Nel, A, Svenson, GJ, Robillard, T, Pellens, R, Grandcolas, P, 2015. Phylogeny of Dictyoptera: dating the origin of cockroaches, praying mantises and termites with molecular data and controlled fossil evidence. Plos one 10(7): e0130127, 27 pp. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" title="Phylogeny of Dictyoptera: dating the origin of cockroaches, praying mantises and termites with molecular data and controlled fossil evidence. Plos one 10 (7): e 0130127, 27 pp." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0130127" year="2015">Legendre et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
placed it as sister to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Methanini">Methanini</taxonomicName>
. As this group of New Caledonian genera cannot be clearly placed within any of the existing subgroups of 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
, we classify it as a separate tribe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Rothisilphini">Rothisilphini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
In addition to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Rothisilphini">Rothisilphini</taxonomicName>
, nine native species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Blattidae</taxonomicName>
are found in New Caledonia, currently placed in the genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Princis" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Maoriblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maoriblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Maoriblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1874" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Isoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Melanozosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Platyzosteria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyzosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Platyzosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Polyzosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyzosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Polyzosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all of the species endemic, except the two 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1874" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Isoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Melanozosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Beccaloni, GW" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Systematics" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" publicationUrl="http://Cockroach.SpeciesFile.org" refId="B4" refString="Beccaloni, GW, 2014. Cockroach Species File Online., http://Cockroach.SpeciesFile.org [ [accessed November 2020] ]" title="Cockroach Species File Online" url="http://Cockroach.SpeciesFile.org" year="2014">Beccaloni 2014</bibRefCitation>
). These species most likely all belong in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Princis, K" editor="Beier, M" journalOrPublisher="W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="1041 - 1224" refId="B70" refString="Princis, K, 1971. Blattariae: Subordo Epilamproidea. Fam.: Ectobiidae. In: Beier, M, Ed., Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 14. W. Junk, 's-Gravenhage: 1041 - 1224" title="Blattariae: Subordo Epilamproidea. Fam.: Ectobiidae." volumeTitle="Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 14." year="1971">Princis (1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Princis, K" journalOrPublisher="Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="513 - 521" refId="B71" refString="Princis, K, 1974. Ergebnisse der Oesterreichischen Neukaledonien-Expedition 1965: Blattariae - Schaben. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien 78: 513 - 521" title="Ergebnisse der Oesterreichischen Neukaledonien-Expedition 1965: Blattariae - Schaben." volume="78" year="1974">1974</bibRefCitation>
) placed four of these species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
, in the genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Princis" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Maoriblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maoriblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Maoriblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in this paper we have assigned these genera to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
(see sections 4.6.5.1., 4.6.5.2., and 4.6.5.4.). Furthermore, prior to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Princis’">Princis'</normalizedToken>
placement of these species, they were placed in genera now included in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Polyzosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyzosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Polyzosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Platyzosteria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyzosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Platyzosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Cutilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cutilia" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Cutilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1874" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Isoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Melanozosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)]. Of these additional New Caledonian blattids, this study included the widespread 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" baseAuthorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria nitida" order="Isoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Melanozosteria nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" baseAuthorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria soror" order="Isoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soror">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Melanozosteria soror</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, firmly placed in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Polyzosteriini">Polyzosteriini</taxonomicName>
. Whether the remaining seven species should be included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Rothisilphini">Rothisilphini</taxonomicName>
, or represent additional dispersal(s) from Australia (or possibly New Zealand if 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Princis’">Princis'</normalizedToken>
placement of four species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Princis" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Maoriblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maoriblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Maoriblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is correct), will have to await further studies.
</paragraph>
